&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366 ; font-size : medium"&gt;Listen Here! Short Story Reading Series&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366 ; font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;"Woody Allen&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;Mr. Big&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;"Arthur Conan Doyle&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;The Red-Headed League&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.newhaventheatercompany.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/inline/images/Listen%20Logo%20copy_0.gif" width="176" height="176" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : 12px"&gt;Doesn't everyone love to be read to!!!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : 12px"&gt;So glad to see the return of this series!&amp;nbsp;The&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : 12px"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : 12px"&gt;New Haven Theater Company puts on a wonderful performance.&amp;nbsp; Join us&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;early at&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : 12px"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6:45&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; for coffee and treats so we do not disrupt the readings.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;&lt;img src="http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/6/f/b/event_38459131.jpeg" width="41" height="42" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px ; float : left"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;New Haven Theater Company and New Haven Review present the Fall 2011 season of &amp;ldquo;Listen Here,&amp;rdquo; a series of short story readings staged at Best Video in Hamden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;The format is simple &amp;ndash; the editors of the New Haven Review pick fine short stories and New Haven Theater Company provide actors to give voice to those works. It all takes place in the comfort of Best Video&amp;rsquo;s new performance space, with fine coffee and treats available as well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #eeeeee"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #993366"&gt;The Listen Here series was featured in an October 2009 New York Times article, &amp;ldquo;Giving Voice to Stories From the Printed Page.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;In an era in which book reading is in decline, it is at once curious and logical that an alliance of New Haven arts groups is tapping the written word in a new venture,&amp;rdquo; the Times&lt;/span&gt; wrote.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><how_to_find_us>will wear the bw scarf</how_to_find_us><event_hosts><event_hosts_item><member_name>Cathy M</member_name><member_id>6563416</member_id></event_hosts_item></event_hosts><maybe_rsvp_count>0</maybe_rsvp_count><waitlist_count>0</waitlist_count><updated>1324157097000</updated><rating><average>5.0</average><count>2</count></rating><group><who>Arts  lovers</who><join_mode>open</join_mode><urlname>Arts-Cultural-Events</urlname><id>1343414</id><group_lat>41.3300018311</group_lat><group_lon>-72.9400024414</group_lon><name>Arts &amp; Creative Cultural Events</name></group><yes_rsvp_count>14</yes_rsvp_count><created>1320276483000</created><visibility>public</visibility><name>Watching the Detectives - Listen Here!</name><id>39729192</id><headcount>8</headcount><utc_offset>-18000000</utc_offset><time>1323992700000</time><event_url>http://www.meetup.com/Arts-Cultural-Events/events/39729192/</event_url></item>